-- Grindrod Bank Lists Preference-Share ETF, Financial Mail Says
-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 2012-03-28T10:57:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/grindrod-bank-lists-preference-share-etf-financial-mail-says.html
Grindrod Ltd. (GND) ’s banking unit listed
the first exchange-traded fund for preference shares in  South
Africa  today,  Financial Mail  reported.  The fund will track the performance of the  Johannesburg
Stock Exchange ’s preference-share index of 17 stocks that pay
dividends, the Johannesburg-based weekly magazine reported,
citing Gareth Stobie, the fund’s manager.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andres R. Martinez in Johannesburg at 
